        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 2:32PM MDT by NWS Pocatello ID</headline>
        <description>At 231 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Spencer, or 9 miles southwest of Idmon, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Idmon, Spencer, and Kilgore.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
